General Information
PRATT and WHITNEY
WASP AIRCRAFT ENGINE
THE PRATT & WHITNEY Model SICC-Wasp Aircraft motor
is a 14 cylinder twin row radial air-cooled engine. This model engine is
used in the twin motor Douglas DC-3 passenger plane. Power produced
by each engine is as follows:
Maximum Rated Horsepower...1200 Brake Horsepower
Normal Take-Off Rating.
1050 Brake Horsepower
Maximum Climb Rating.
900 Brake Horsepower

The
gross weight of the Douglas plane is
12 tons.
• The cruising speed of the Douglas
plane equipped with these engines and
propellers is 190 miles per hour. Maxi-
mum speed is 228 miles per hour. The
plane has a service ceiling of 22,000
feet with full load, and can climb to
11,000 feet with only one engine oper-
ating.
Rate of climb is 1000 feet per
minute.

feathering propellers of three blade
design are used with this engine. The
